==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electrotonus
<hw>E`lec*trot"o*nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
combining form <ets>electro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ tension.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The modified condition of a nerve, when a
constant current of electricity passes through any part of it. See
<er>Anelectrotonus</er>, and <er>Catelectrotonus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electrotype</ent>⟦br⟧
